# Playtest for Atlas

*Grapeshot Games
* 5/10 -Steam 6/10 -Me
* https://www.playatlas.com/

**Question:** During your playtesting where the rules of the game understandable? If not, what was not clear.
> _Answer: The game never really explained what i should do or what i should show interest in it just told me basics of build this this is the menu and heres how to leave. From there i was on my own.

**Question:** During gameplay did you notice anything that shouldn't be in the game or could be removed and it wouldn't effect game play?
> _Answer: Food levels , most players kill themselves rather than focus on eating healthy and varying their meals because they can respawn and theres no repercussion asides from picking up their materials

**Question:** Is this game balanced? If not, what is the target audience for this game based on that imbalance?
> _Answer:_ No, For a solo player its horribly inbalanced it favors large factions or corporations instead.

**Question:** Does the timing of this game appear to be about right for this type of game?
> _Answer: I Dont think so theres plenty of other faction games like Ark and right now the focus is on battle royales this game takes time and investment.

**Question:** During gameplay did the mechanics and theme go together and reinforce each other?
> _Answer: This game is very hard its meant to be, almost everything is meant to kill you and alot of the game revolves around traveling the open sea and upgrading  or building things and its a huge world focused on factions and survival.

**Question:** Did you have fun playing this game?
> _Answer:_ Yes i like difficult games and this game does let you free explore and face various dangers like a pirate would.

**Question:** During gameplay what problems or issues seemed to happen and how did you get them to reoccur?
> _Answer: If your boat was anchored and another player jumped on it theyd get stuck in a way to prevent griefing the only way to get off was to die or they raise anchor but no one wanted to lose their boat.
often when switching servers you might clip or have trouble, fall off the boat and struggle to get on etc.
